 In these times, fierce wars raged among many nobles who fought for the throne.
 The Three Kingdoms period was one of the bloodiest eras in the history of ancient China, with thousands of people dying in the battle for the highest throne in the great palace of Xi'an.
 There are a lot of social and political effects like the use of the metric system, a shift from absolutism to republicanism and nationalism, and the belief that the land belongs to the people and not to one ruler alone.
