 Subsistence farming is agriculture that aims to produce just enough food to meet the needs of the farmer and his or her family.
 Subsistence agriculture is a simple, often organic farming method that uses saved, indigenous seed stock and combines with crop rotation or other relatively simple techniques to maximize yield.
 In the past, most farmers practiced subsistence farming and in many developing countries this is still the case.
 Subcultures bring together like-minded people who feel neglected by societal norms, and allow them to develop a sense of identity.
 Subcultures can be distinguished from other subcultures in terms of age, ethnicity, class, location and/or gender of the members.
 The properties that distinguish a subculture as such can be linguistic, aesthetic, religious, political, sexual or geographical or a combination of these factors.
 Members of a subculture often signal their membership by an unmistakable and symbolic style, which includes fashion, habits and jargon.
