 Wolf children may have experienced severe child abuse or traumatic experiences before they were abandoned or ran away.
 Others may have been raised by animals; some may have lived alone in the wild.
 If it was raised completely by animals, the wild child shows behaviors (within the limits of his physical abilities) that are almost completely in accordance with those of his specific caretaker, such as its fear or indifference towards humans.
