 Aristotle, a philosopher, proposed the theory that all things are made up of a mixture of one or more of four elements: earth, water, air, and fire.
 This corresponded more to the four states of aggregation (in the same order): solid, liquid, gas and plasma. He also put forward the theory that they change into new substances to form what we see.
 Alloys are basically a mixture of two or more metals. Remember that there are many elements in the periodic table.
 Elements like calcium and potassium are considered metals. Of course, there are other metals like silver and gold.
 There are also alloys that contain small amounts of nonmetallic elements such as carbon.
