 When all available resources are effectively utilized across all departments of an organization, creativity and ingenuity can emerge.
 As a result, the collective work of an organization to overcome an obstacle can lead to a new innovative method to meet customer needs.
 Before an organization can be innovative, management must develop a culture of innovation, shared knowledge, and organizational learning.
 Angel (2006) explains the Continuum Concept as a method to help organizations become more effective.
