 The official currency of the Falkland Islands is the Falkland Pound (FKP), whose value is fixed in line with the value of the British Pound (GBP).
 Money can be exchanged at the only bank on the island, which is located in Stanley opposite the FIC West Store.
 The British Pound is generally accepted everywhere on the islands and at Stanley credit cards are also widely accepted. US dollars are also often accepted.
 On the remote islands, credit cards are probably not accepted, although British and US currency can be accepted; inquire in advance with the owners which method of payment is accepted.
 It is almost impossible to exchange the currency of the Falkland Islands outside the islands themselves, so you should exchange the money before leaving the island.x
 Since Montevideo is located south of the equator, it is summer there when it is winter in the northern hemisphere and vice versa.
 Montevideo is located in the subtropics. In the summer months, temperatures above +30 ° C are common.
 Winter can be deceivingly cold: Temperatures rarely go below freezing, but wind and humidity make it feel colder than the thermometer indicates.
 There are no distinct rainy or dry seasons: the amount of rainfall is more or less the same throughout the year.
 Although many of the animals in the park are used to seeing people, the wildlife is still wild and should not be fed or disturbed.
 According to the Park Authority, visitors must keep at least 100 yards/meters away from bears and wolves and 25 yards/meters away from all other wild animals!
 No matter how peaceful bison, moose, elk, bears and practically all large animals may appear, they can still attack.
 Dozens of visitors are injured every year because they don't keep their distance. These animals are large, wild, and potentially dangerous, so give them plenty of space.
 Also be aware that smells can attract bears and other wildlife, so avoid carrying or cooking strongly scented foods and keep a clean camp.
