 For example, castle tours in the Loire Valley, in the Rhine Valley or a cruise to interesting cities on the Danube or a boat trip along the Erie Canal.
 They also represent popular hiking and biking routes.
 In Christianity, Christmas is one of the most important holidays and is considered the birthday of Jesus.
 Many of the traditions around the holiday have been adopted by non-believers in Christian and non-Christian countries around the world.
 There is a tradition of spending Easter night at some open place to see the sunrise.
 There are of course Christian-theological explanations for this tradition, but it could also be a pre-Christian spring and fertility ritual.
 Traditional churches often hold an Easter Vigil on Saturday evening, during the Easter weekend, with the celebrations of the communities often beginning at midnight, celebrating the resurrection of Christ.
 All the animals that originally arrived on the islands either swam, flew or washed ashore.
 Due to the great distance from the mainland, mammals were unable to make the journey, making the giant tortoise the main source of food on the Galapagos Islands.
 Since the first humans set foot on the Galapagos Islands, many mammals have been introduced, including goats, horses, rats, cats and dogs.
 If you visit the Arctic or Antarctic regions in winter, you will experience the polar night, which means that the sun does not rise above the horizon.
 This is a good opportunity to see the Northern Lights, as the sky is dark more or less all night.
 Since the areas are sparsely populated and light pollution is therefore often not a problem, you can also enjoy the starry sky.
 The Japanese work culture is more hierarchical and formal than what Westerners may be used to.
 Suits are part of the standard business attire and colleagues address each other by their family names or job titles.
 Harmony in the workplace is of crucial importance, with the focus being on group performance rather than on praise for individual achievements.
 Often, employees must seek the approval of their superiors for all decisions they make, and they are expected to follow their bosses' orders without question.
